> What about users grabbing Linux for the first time? Are you gonna force
> them to get a old version and patch it until eternity? That is one hell of
> a way to welcome new users...
They would at worst have to get a 2-day old version, and apply one
or maybe two patches.  Not too bad, and they would learn to use
patch too, very useful.  Development kernels aren't meant for
linux newbies anyway.  A kernel-hacker newbie can safely be forced
to learn the use of patch.
